name: Meet Dick
description:
Most days, Dick is a fine upstanding citizen, responsible in every way. But once a year towards the end of August, Dick becomes antsy. As Labor Day approaches Dick dons a red cape and turns his back on the world. Dick slides into an alternate reality where anything goes - and yes, occasionally Dick makes the angels cry. 

After all, there's a little Dick in all of us - and don't forget, we all love Dicks.

When viewed in person, they embody the hours of work that go into creating a hand carved edition. Go ahead, run your fingers over it, linoleum is meant to be walked on as flooring so rest assured this piece could be the beginning of your "hands on" collection.

name: Seed of Civilization
description: 4 color linoleum block print Signed/Numbered limited edition of 100 Canson Edition antique white paper stock Created for the Screens & Suds Chicago event, The Seed of Civiliation acknowledges the humble beginnings of brewing and the theory that the brewing of beer actually spurred on civilization as we know it. "May beer have helped lead to the rise of civilization? It's a possibility, some archaeologists say. Their argument is that Stone Age farmers were domesticating cereals not so much to fill their stomachs but to lighten their heads, by turning the grains into beer. That has been their take for more than 50 years, and now one archaeologist says the evidence is getting stronger." Read more...
